  "notes": "Mapping covers all 91 raw entries from brand-colors.md (76 solid hexes + 15 gradient lines). Solid-color duplicates collapsed to one token: #7C30F7≈#7C2FF7 (brand-600); #1E1E1E≈#222222 (text-primary/neutral); #343B4B≈#313745 (dark surface/border); #727272≈#717171, #616161≈#626262 (neutrals); #61708E≈#697586 (text-subtle); #FE2E2E≈#FF0000 (danger). The #DAE3FE->#E9EFFD light-blue card gradient appears 15 times (lines 60-74) with trivially different stop percentages (-0.02% to 100.01%) — all normalized to one token gradient-card-blue. Seven #FEBBBA->#FF928E coral gradients (lines 80-86) differ only by angle/stop and are all severity-area chart fills. LIKELY-UNUSED / hard-to-place in the four supplied screens: #B7883B (bronze/gold — no on-screen usage found, possibly a legacy award/badge accent); #001219 (deepest teal-black — reserved dark surface, not clearly visible); #8145FF, #A989C8, #CFC1D8, #6C5D82, #897398, #8E7A9D (muted-purple family — plausible dark-UI accents/tints but not distinctly identifiable in these specific screens). Severity semantics confirmed from the Employee-exposure badges (Medium=yellow, High=orange, Critical=red) and Threat-overview legends (Low=green added). Brand primary is #7C2FF7 (links/active) with #5B3DF5 as the CTA-button/gradient base."
